From Chris Crayton Subject Date is stuck On Michael Shapiro had the unmitigated gall to say this MS The DOS system date has a twenty four hour clock and a rollover MS When the system crosses midnight the rollover bit is turned MS Subsequent reads of the time add There's no change possible MS This information was current up through DOS I've not checked to MS see whether it applies to later Just a small tidbit with the advent of DOS and later versions MS added a small feature to the DOS time If a program sets the DOS clock via DOS system services then DOS will set the BIOS clock to the same This breaks the isolation between the two clocks that used to ensure that errors in the DOS clock did not bleed over into the BIOS Sometimes the Microsoft people just don't think Fact Mickey Mouse wears a Al Gore Blue Wave QWK The Ozone Hole BBS A Private Bulletin Board Service Full Service Nodes USRobotics bps Gigs Files SKYDIVE New Orleans RIME Network Mail HUB Usenet Newsgroups Please route all questions or inquiries to